TY  - JOUR
AU  - Collin-Dufresne, Pierre
AU  - Johannes, Michael
AU  - Lochstoer, Lars A.
T1  - Asset Pricing When ‘This Time Is Different’
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhw084
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 30
IS  - 2
SP  - 505
EP  - 535
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Recent evidence suggests that younger people update beliefs in response to aggregate shocks more than older people. We embed this generational learning bias in an equilibrium model in which agents have recursive preferences and are uncertain about exogenous aggregate dynamics. The departure from rational expectations is statistically modest, but generates high average risk premiums varying at generational frequencies, a positive relation between past returns and agents’ future return forecasts, and substantial and persistent over- and undervaluation. Consistent with the model, the price-dividend ratio is empirically more sensitive to macroeconomic shocks when the fraction of young in the population is higher.Received September 14, 2015; editorial decision March 10, 2016 by Editor Stefan Nagel
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhw084
ER  - 



