TY  - JOUR
AU  - Menkhoff, Lukas
AU  - Sarno, Lucio
AU  - Schmeling, Maik
AU  - Schrimpf, Andreas
T1  - Currency Value
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhw067
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 30
IS  - 2
SP  - 416
EP  - 441
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We assess the properties of currency value strategies based on real exchange rates. We find that real exchange rates have predictive power for the cross-section of currency excess returns. However, adjusting real exchange rates for key country-specific fundamentals (productivity, the quality of export goods, net foreign assets, and output gaps) better isolates information related to the currency risk premium. In turn, the resultant measure of currency value displays considerably stronger predictive power for currency excess returns. Finally, the predictive information content in our currency value measure is distinct from that embedded in popular currency strategies, such as carry and momentum.Received June 26, 2015; accepted June 8, 2016 by Editor Stefan Nagel.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhw067
ER  - 



